{meta: title Faded Coat Of Blue}
{meta: artist The Waller Brothers}
{meta: composer J.H. McNaughton}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]My brave man sleeps in his faded coat of [F]blue
[C]In a lonely grave unknown lies a heart that beat so [G7]true
[C]He sat faint and hungry among the Spanish [F]braves
[C]And they laid him sad and lonely [G7]within a nameless [C]grave
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[F]No more the bugle calls the weary one
[G7]Rest noble spirit in a grave unknown
[C]For we'll find you and know you among the good and [F]true
[C]Where a robe of white is given for a [G7]faded coat of [C]blue
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]He cried give me water and just a little crumb
[C]And my mother she would bless you through all the years to [G7]come
[C]And tell my sweet sister so gentle good and [F]true
[C]That I'll meet her up in heaven in [G7]my faded coat of [C]blue
{end_of_verse}

